        "answer": "The reasoning is flawed because it relies on topography, the observable form of the behavior, rather than function. Identical topographies can serve different functions. Student A's pattern suggests an attention-maintained function, while Student B's pattern (continuing despite ignoring) suggests an automatic function. The team should conduct a functional behavioral assessment for each student to identify the maintaining antecedents and consequences before designing any intervention.",
